{"entity":{"id":"recUoGyebP8lze1GQ","type":"chapter","slug":"recUoGyebP8lze1GQ","label":"Job.16","rawId":"recUoGyebP8lze1GQ","book":{"id":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","type":"book","slug":"job","label":"Job","subtitle":"Poetry-Wisdom","count":1070,"description":"42 chapters, 190 people, 6 places"}},"stats":{"verses":22,"people":2,"places":0,"events":1},"nodes":[{"id":"recUoGyebP8lze1GQ","type":"chapter","group":"focus","label":"Job.16","slug":"job_16","score":22},{"id":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","type":"book","group":"book","label":"Job","slug":"job","score":1070},{"id":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"God","slug":"god_1324","score":3},{"id":"recKXL1QrW8qTw5Ux","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"Job","slug":"job_1639","score":1},{"id":"recMNT9RB1RJiLlYW","type":"event","group":"event","label":"Job's Trial","slug":"event-117","score":22}],"links":[{"source":"recUoGyebP8lze1GQ","target":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","label":"part of"},{"source":"recUoGyebP8lze1GQ","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUoGyebP8lze1GQ","target":"recKXL1QrW8qTw5Ux","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUoGyebP8lze1GQ","target":"recMNT9RB1RJiLlYW","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recvvBPmmDI876SD5","ref":"Job.16.1","text":"Then Job answered and said,","year":-1520},{"id":"recHyaKXQsEYoj7s6","ref":"Job.16.2","text":"I have heard many such things: miserable comforters are ye all.","year":-1520},{"id":"recWYghT3Ij91dAxG","ref":"Job.16.3","text":"Shall vain words have an end? or what emboldeneth thee that thou answerest?","year":-1520},{"id":"recI8OUpsdhupLZBO","ref":"Job.16.4","text":"I also could speak as ye do: if your soul were in my soul’s stead, I could heap up words against you, and shake mine head at you.","year":-1520},{"id":"reciutbQOchYTOKKt","ref":"Job.16.5","text":"But I would strengthen you with my mouth, and the moving of my lips should asswage your grief.","year":-1520},{"id":"recJauiZxWniCicfH","ref":"Job.16.6","text":"Though I speak, my grief is not asswaged: and though I forbear, what am I eased?","year":-1520},{"id":"recozVhNqlt1QaxYC","ref":"Job.16.7","text":"But now he hath made me weary: thou hast made desolate all my company.","year":-1520},{"id":"reccRPZdEQjCIvXmc","ref":"Job.16.8","text":"And thou hast filled me with wrinkles, which is a witness against me: and my leanness rising up in me beareth witness to my face.","year":-1520}]}
